Co-convener of the Bring Back Our Girls group, Aisha Yesufu has blamed the recent killing of scores of Plateau villagers by suspected herdsmen on the incompetence of President Muhammadu Buhari’s administration. The activist insisted that the Buhari’s administration has no respect for citizen’s lives and should be voted out in the next general elections. “President Muhammadu Buhari, your government has shown zero respect for Nigerian lives. You have not protected Nigerian lives,” Yesufu tweeted on Monday. “You have been an utter and total disaster. You have to go.” She further lamented that “Government’s incompetence has led to citizens taking the laws into their hands and killing fellow citizens who are also victims.” “When there is no equity and justice, anarchy prevails.” Read More: PDP blames Buhari over Plateau killings The Police Command in Plateau had on Sunday confirmed the killing of 86 people in attacks on Razat, Ruku, Nyarr, Kura and Gana-Ropp villages of Gashish District in Barkin Ladi Local Government Area of the state. Buhari said the killings were “painful and regrettable”. He vowed that his administration would not rest until the murderers and sponsors are brought to justice. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .